-- BTG ‘Hasn’t Been Notified’ About Executives Seeking Compensation
-- B y   K a r e n   E e u w e n s
-- 2012-07-22T18:09:39Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-07-22/btg-hasn-t-been-notified-about-executives-seeking-compensation.html
Banco BTG Pactual SA “hasn’t been
notified” about executives including Grupo Silvio Santos’
former chief executive officer, Luiz Sandoval, seeking
compensation, Leandro Buarque, a BTG spokesman, said by e-mail.  Veja magazine columnist Lauro Jardim today reported that
Sandoval and former executives of Banco Panamericano SA are
seeking 150 million reais ($74 million) of workers’ compensation
from BTG.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Karen Eeuwens in London at 
